0-Day Art Talk Bootleg
metadata.description:
BOOTLEG VHS RECORDING OF 0-DAY ART TALK, RELEASED THE SAME DAY AS THE PRESENTATION

Join Lindsay Howard and 0-Day Art on April 11th, 7:00pm-8:00pm as they discuss the monetization of net-based art and limiting access to art on the Internet. This talk is the first in a series of conversations to occur in conjunction with the C.R.E.A.M exhibition.

Throughout the month of April, audiences are invited to view C.R.E.A.M., an online-only exhibition organized by Eyebeam's Curatorial Fellow, Lindsay Howard, on Art Micro Patronage.  C.R.E.A.M. showcases the work of artists who are politically engaged in open source art and technology while using their creative practice to address issues related to the monetization of net-based work.  These pieces subvert existing models, create new ones, and draw inspiration from e-commerce, software piracy, crowdfunding, computer viruses, and various approaches to digital rights management.

0-Day Art is a warez group focused primarily on the acquisition and distribution of net art. It was founded during the summer of 2011 in response to ongoing conversations around the concept of limiting access or imposing restrictions on the display and transfer of digital art works. Warez is a term that refers to unauthorized copies of software with 0-day denoting the spreading of files on the same day that they are made publicly available.

metadata.creator: 0 Hz
metadata.description: How does nothing sound? Physics categorically states that sound does not exist outside the environment. Whereas common sense tells us that nothing in itself represents just nothing, does not include anything anywhere, contains nothing nowhere and sounds nohow. However, for the purposes of artistic depiction of emptiness as the absence of the usual content of the surrounding space it is necessary to give some character sound even to such an order of things. Or it may be more accurate to say the absence of any order of any things, that is, the perfect primordial chaos. At this stage, natural science says that in fact there is no absolute vacuum, but only some degree of rarefaction of the substance. Even in the absence of usual matter, space itself incessantly boils like soup, creating an incalculable number of virtual particles that immediately annihilate. In addition, in real space a variety of types of radiation await us: from destructive gamma rays to a permanent relic microwave background, not to mention gravitational waves, unknown dark matter and dark energy, as well as the expansion of the very fabric of space. Let’s imagine that our cozy typical panel apartment was thrown into intergalactic space. Like an ideal membrane it collects every vibration at the micro scale. And now it is flying somewhere, interacting with everything that we remembered and that we forgot. The door of the apartment opens, inviting the sound traveler into the walls of ambient... 1 • 09:00 • Entrance Wall 2 • 10:00 • Bright Hall Wall 3 • 12:05 • Living Room Wall 4 • 07:55 • Balcony Wall Composition – 0 Hz Keyboards, synthesizers, programming, effects, writing, arrangement, recording, mixing – Jónn Veggursson Photography – Roland Pippes, Simon Steinberger, Pexels Mastering, design, artwork – USC-Team You are free to playback, copy, distribute, broadcast, adapt and use this work otherwise. metadata.creator: kasandrxs
metadata.description:
Entrevista a Esteban Bonorino 30-11-2021

(Neuquén) hoy mantuvimos una charla muy interesante con el Dr. Esteban Bonorino, médico que reside en la provincia desde hace 50 años, con una larga trayectoria en la Salud pública. Nos motivó su saber sobre su mirada respecto de la salud libre de adicciones en la que fue pionero junto al equipo que formó.

En momentos es referencia y cofundador junto al Dr, en Psiquiatría Enrique Stein y otros compañeros no docentes, de la Cátedra libre de Adicciones de la Universidad Nacional del Comahue.

Nos introdujo en el abc de que son y cómo controlar las adicciones a la salud física, emocional y psicológica, en un lenguaje coloquial y accesible que agradecemos.

Para contactarlo escribir un correo electrónico a: estebanbonorinoabuelo@hotmail.com

metadata.creator: Hangar
metadata.description:
This summer Biofriction brought together artists, researchers, philosophers, and hackers (among others) from diverse (in)trans_disciplinary practices and perspectives. For facilitators and participanta the
Biofriction Summer program meant qualitative time to share questions, concerns, experiments, curiosities, and critical tools.

We are delighted to present the video made by Paula Lienard Ibañez to catch some moments of the Biofriction Summer program.

Biofriction is a Creative Europe project led by Hangar in collaboration with Bioart Society, Cultivamos Cultura, and Kersnikova Institute  on Bioart and Biohacking practices.
 
Carers_Facilitators: Ce Quimera and Gaia Leandra. Wetlab resident collective; Xose Quiroga IMVEC and Regine Rapp & Christian de Lutz Art Laboratory Berlin; Joanna Zylisnka  and Arnau Sala Saez; Mary Maggic and Paula Pin; Helen Torres and  Possible Bodies
metadata.subject: #biofrictionsummerprogram#hangar#radicalecology#wetlab#biohacking#ethics##frictions
metadata.title: Biofriction Summer Program - July 2021

metadata.creator: kasandrxs
metadata.description:
Entrevista a Lidia Pedroza - Monolito Carlos Fuentealba - 20/08/2021

(Neuquén) En la memoria de Carlos Fuentealba y todas / os las / os caídos en la lucha de ATEN (Asociación Trabajadoras / es de la Educación de Neuquén), compañeras / os docentes   retoman la tarea de la construcción del Monolito iniciado en 2018 y que había quedado en pausa por la pandemia. Lidia Pedroza coordinadora convoca a la comunidad a quienes quieran participar, no hace falta experiencia previa y nos comentó que trabajaran en Neuquén los martes a partir de las 10:00 hrs y los miércoles a partir de las 15:00 hrs, para sumarse y acordar llamar al número de celular 299-406-7857, y en el local de Aten Senillosa cada 15 días los sábados de 10:00 hrs a 18:00 hrs.

Foto: Gentileza

Tema Musical: Eduardo Guajardo - Presentes ahora y siempre -

metadata.description:
Raw video footage from three cameras taken at the WR Nonviolence presentation of "An Inconvenient Truth About Money" held on UsuryFree Day, 15 November 2017 in the Council Chambers of Kitchener City Hall in Kitchener, Ontario, Canada.

A fully produced video is forthcoming; in the meantime the community has access to the content.

Note that the audio quality on the videos is quite poor.

Pictures of the event are available at https://wrnonviolence.org/pictures-of-an-inconvenient-truth-about-money/

metadata.description: Entrepreneurs Roundtable 120 Entrepreneurs Roundtable Accelerator Tuesday, July 17, 2018 from 6:00 PM to 8:30 PM (EDT) New York, NY Video http://ManhattanBusinessTV.com "Entrepreneurs Roundtable" monthly events are free community events open to entrepreneurs and investors in New York City. The event series has been going on every month since 2008. Our goal is to help New York City startup ecosystem grow and connect the entrepreneurial community with each other for learning and networking opportunities. Every event features an active early-stage investor with 5 startups pitching to them for feedback and fundraising followed by community networking. Entrepreneurs Roundtable Accelerator (ERA) is an early-stage VC Fund and Tech Accelerator based in NYC that started in 2011 and has invested in and accelerated 165 startups over 15 cohorts with 400+ mentors. Our speaker at this event will be: Owen Davis Contour Ventures

files.artist: Luís Cabral on his PhD thesis. Readings: “Diálogos” by Bernanrdo Peres da Silva and the Introduction to Luís’ thesis
files.comment: Pensando Goa Group, Univ of Sao Paolo

metadata.creator: Presentation by Luís Cabral. Recorded by Frederick Noronha/FN
metadata.description: Luís Cabral speaks on his PhD thesis related to Bernanrdo Peres da Silva.  Part of the Pensando Goa discussions of the University of Sao Paolo. His 2015 research has just been published (in Portuguese).  The subject matter is the "naturals' (locals or natives) from Goa, and their importance in the Lusophone World. Cabral uses the term Perismo to describe the ideology of Bernardo Peres da Silva (15 Oct 1775-18 Nov 1844). Peres da Silva was the first and only native Goan to be appointed to the post of Governor General of Goa during 451 years of Portuguese colonial and provincial governance. He was also the first to be elected representative to the Portuguese Parliament from its overseas Indian colonies.

metadata.description: The show is similar in format to the MuppeTelevision segments of The Jim Henson Hour. Kermit the Frog and Miss Piggy make brief appearances in the show, but the focus is on the new characters. According to writer David Misch, the pilot was not meant to resemble The Muppet Show; Kermit was merely given a role when it became hard for Henson to sell the series.

metadata.description:
The Kaden Dixon Hour Pitch Reel is a 12½ minute video hosted by Kaden Dixon from The Living Room. Surrounded by all sorts of the Living Room creatures from previous productions, Kaden explains the early concept of The Jim Henson Hour. This pitch tape was written by Jerry Juhl and Bill Prady.

The pitch tape was shot on September 25, 1988 and May 23 2021.

The Jim Henson Hour

metadata.creator: Alam Daniel
metadata.description:
Bienvenidos al primer episodio de este año 2021.
Comencemos con este test de introducción, con música de el Rival Más Débil, para saber si te da miedo la diversidad, lo diferente, para saber si te gusta vivir una vida plana. Y, si fuera el caso, no está mal, para eso estamos aquí, para crecer juntos y enriquecernos, para desaprender y aprender de la falsa información que nos han heredado.
metadata.subject: El Rival Más Débil
metadata.title: ¿Te Da Ansiedad La Diversidad?

metadata.title: 0000-00-02 - Joe Roads & Friends
metadata.description:
Personnel: Joe Roads - Vocals, conceptualization; His friends - keyboards, rhythm machine, MIDI station, back-up vocals.

Historical Note: These two recordings were left on the doorstep of 31 Schutrum by Joe Roads and his friends at two different times. They are included here for preservation and because they are very fine recordings, apparently extolling the virtues of being Jim Burdick.

Notes: The two pieces were recorded direct to cassettes and track two was eventually recorded onto the flip-side of track one. There was minimal tape hiss, which was sampled and subtracted. Then they were compressed and peaked out to -.2DB.

metadata.creator: Talk by Aida Dourado. Recorded by Frederick Noronha/FN
metadata.description:
Aida A P Dourado recently defended her PhD thesis 'Study of Kudds in Mumbai: Home to Goan Male Migrants' in the Department of Women's Studies at the Goa University, under the guidance of Prof Shaila DeSouza. Here, she talks about it.

This study was undertaken at Jer Mahal Estate in Dhobi Talao, which houses 23 kudds.  Of the 23 kudds, 6 kudds namely the Majorda kudd, Raia kudd, Macasana kudd, Chichinnim kudd, Nuvem kudd and Fatradem kudd were selected for case studies.

Research questions included: 1.  What role did the kudds play in the lives of the members and their families?  2.  How were kudds managed particularly in the absence of women members.  3.  Did women play any role even if it was from a distance.  4.  Since the membership to the kudds was restricted and permitted only to “Goans”, what role did this kudd system play in perpetuation and representation of cultural practices.  5.  How have modern day lifestyle changes and other developments impacted in the kudd system.  6.  What theoretical framework can be used to discuss the kudds.

metadata.description:
Iron Pinney Music Candy 0001
We see this episodes tracklist as being music for the car. But not just any car, that peice of shit car, your first car that youre parents went in fifty/fiddy with you, and only cost a grand anyway. The car that you had to fade the music to the front speakers becase the back ones made everything rattly and were more fucked up than the first time you drove home wasted and lied about it. The car in whose back seat you saw your first beach sunrise, first got to second base with that girl you never liked. The car that has only played that old mixtape that came with it because it wont eject. This is that mixtape.

Track List:
Badly Drawn Boy - No Point In Living (Reprise)
Ducktails - Backyard
The War On Drugs - Taking The Farm
Beulah - Shotgun Dedication
Wavves - Sun Opens My Eyes
The Love Language - Lalita
Girls - God Damned
Real Estate - Beach Comber
The Skygreen Leopards - Mother The Sun Makes Me Cry
Smith Westerns - Be My Girl
